**[1851, 06-26] Ms.A.1.2.20.59**

GT to WLG; At sea

“In my berth, I had some hours of indescribable melancholy, and felt
most severely the pangs of separation. The pain I now feel will, I know,
lessen as I proceed, but my love will continue in all its strength. I
have been ten-thousand times over repaid for all my time and labours in
America, by the joy of meeting with you and the noble beings by whom you
are surrounded and sustained …”


